<br>
Mages swear by it.   Most high end mages I know can fairly quickly regen mana by canni-petting.  With Summoning Efficiency focus, a mage can actually summon a pet for way less mana than is returned by reclaim.   So, they summon-reclaim-summon-reclaim till FM.<br>
<br>
If your animation is about to die, A well-timed Reclaim assures that it won't die uselessly.   This especially becomes important at high-50s, when you face enraging mobs often.   Untill you get to 65 and train Animation Empathy 3, you cannot back off your pet - and unless your animation is in mob's rear arc, it'll most likely die.   Hitting Reclaim when you see enrage message can at high levels mean a nice hunk of free mana.  Main problem is unless you got a clicky, you can't really afford a spell slot for RE. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Coercer, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
